  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "\n<p><b>Type:</b> Ninjutsu </p>\n<p><b>Rank:</b> 6 (Spell Level 3)</p>\n<p><b>Chakra Cost:</b> 5</p>\n\n<p><b>Learn DC:</b> 19 | <b>Successes:</b> 2</p>\n<p><b>Perform:</b> 7 | <b>Perform DC:</b> 19</p>\n\n<p><b>Components:</b> F, H</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>You make a ranged touch attack, which binds the target to a nearby object or suface, immobilizing it as iron wires wrap tightly around them. Though flying targets relying on wings will fall, they will be held at maximum range unless you decide to let them go. A bound creature also suffers a -4 penalty to Defense while it is bound.<br><br>The target remains that way as long as you keep the wire used in your hand and concentrate, though they can make an Escape Artist check (DC 30) or a Strength check (DC 25) to break free. As an attack action while holding a creature in Kousen Shibari no Jutsu, you can pull on the wires to deal 1d4+1 slashing damage to the target as the wires cut into their flesh (an opposed Strength check can negate this damage).</p>\n\n\n\n",
      "summary": "",
      "instructions": ""
    },
